<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6608] GroovyLexer#require(...) method execution may have a NULL parser</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6608</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The issue if found in Groovy Eclipse.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test Scenario:&lt;br/&gt;
def scanFolders(){&lt;br/&gt;
	doThis(&lt;br/&gt;
		~&quot;(?i)^sometext$&quot;,	// SMART TAB FAILS AFTER HERE.&lt;br/&gt;
		// ESCAPE THE DOLLAR SIGN AND THE WORLD SPINS AGAIN&lt;br/&gt;
		~&quot;(?i)^&lt;em&gt;vti&lt;/em&gt;&quot;, 		// Sub-folder exclusion Filter&lt;br/&gt;
		null,&lt;br/&gt;
		null&lt;br/&gt;
	);&lt;br/&gt;
};&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Press enter at the end of the line and observe NPE in the log. NPE occurs in the method due to the null parser field.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The body of GroovyLexer#require(...) has a reference to parser that may not be set all the time. Furthermore the TODO comment in the method body states that error reporting should be done without parser usage: &quot;Direct to a common error handler, rather than through the parser&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
